# A to Z Meta Publisher — Cursor Agent Rules

## Project Context
This is an internal social media management tool for **AtoZ Flooring Solutions** 
(atozflooringsolutions.com.au), an insurance replacement flooring business in 
Bundaberg, Queensland, Australia.

The backend is a **Flask + SQLite** app running on localhost:4000 with existing routes:
- /admin — main admin panel
- /admin-scheduled-posts — SQLite post queue
- /admin-draft-posts — draft approval workflow
- /admin-competitor-insights — competitor signal snapshots
- /admin-post-performance — post impressions/reach/engagement
- /supplier-email-upload — .eml/.msg/.zip ingestion

The frontend needs to be rebuilt as a **modern React/Next.js UI** that interfaces 
with these existing Flask API endpoints.

---

## Tech Stack (STRICT — do not deviate)

### Core
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v3+ with custom AtoZ brand config
- **Components**: shadcn/ui (latest) — install via `npx shadcn@latest add`

### Animation & Motion
- **Framer Motion** — for page transitions, card hovers, modal slides
- Use `AnimatePresence` for route transitions
- Use `motion.div` with `whileHover` for thumbnail cards

### Icons
- **Lucide React** — ONLY use lucide-react, no other icon library
- Preferred icons: `Instagram`, `Facebook`, `Calendar`, `Image`, `Send`, 
  `Clock`, `TrendingUp`, `Eye`, `Heart`, `MessageCircle`

### Fonts
- **Geist Sans** (via `next/font/google`) as the primary font
- **Geist Mono** for timestamps, IDs, and code blocks

---

## Brand Configuration

### tailwind.config.ts — extend colors with:
```ts
colors: {
  brand: {
    primary: '#1e3a5f',    // AtoZ deep navy blue
    accent: '#e8a020',     // AtoZ warm amber/gold
    surface: '#f8f9fa',    // clean off-white background
    card: '#ffffff',
    muted: '#6b7280',      // zinc-500 for secondary text
  },
  platform: {
    facebook: '#1877F2',
    instagram: '#E1306C',
    'instagram-end': '#833AB4',
  }
}
```

### Design Principles
- **White space first** — generous padding (p-6, p-8 on cards)
- **Card-based layout** — every section lives in a rounded-2xl shadow-sm card
- **Sidebar navigation** — collapsible, 64px icon-only / 240px expanded
- **NO dark mode by default** — light, clean, professional

---

## Component Architecture

### Layout
```
AppShell
├── Sidebar (platform tabs: Instagram | Facebook | Scheduler | Analytics)
├── MainContent
│   ├── PageHeader (title + action button)
│   ├── ContentGrid (thumbnail grid OR table view toggle)
│   └── RightPanel (PhoneMockup preview, collapsible)
└── ToastProvider (shadcn Toaster)
```

### Required Custom Components to Build
1. **`<PhoneMockup>`** — CSS iPhone frame using `aspect-ratio: 9/19.5`, 
   `rounded-[3rem]`, inner shadow, status bar. Live-renders post preview.
2. **`<PostThumbnailCard>`** — 1:1 image grid card with:
   - Platform badge (FB blue / IG gradient pill)
   - Status badge (Scheduled/Draft/Published) using shadcn `<Badge>`
   - Hover overlay with engagement stats using Framer Motion
   - `scheduled_at` formatted with `date-fns`
3. **`<PlatformTab>`** — Sidebar tab with platform color indicator dot
4. **`<ScheduleTimeline>`** — Horizontal scroll timeline of upcoming posts
5. **`<CompetitorCard>`** — Bento-style card for competitor signal data

---

## API Integration

All API calls go to `http://localhost:4000` (Flask backend).
Use **SWR** for data fetching with 30-second revalidation:
```ts
const { data, mutate } = useSWR('/api/scheduled-posts', fetcher, {
  refreshInterval: 30000
})
```

Create a Next.js API proxy layer at `app/api/[...path]/route.ts` to 
forward requests to Flask, avoiding CORS issues.

### Key endpoints to proxy:
- `GET /admin-scheduled-posts` → scheduled queue
- `GET /admin-draft-posts` → drafts for approval
- `POST /admin-draft-posts/:id/approve` → approve draft
- `GET /admin-competitor-insights` → competitor data
- `GET /admin-post-performance` → engagement metrics

---

## Page Specifications

### Dashboard (`/`)
- 4-stat bento grid: Total Scheduled, Published This Week, Avg Engagement, 
  Competitor Alerts
- Recent posts thumbnail grid (last 12)
- Upcoming schedule timeline (next 7 days)

### Posts (`/posts`)
- Toggle: Grid view (thumbnails) | Table view
- Filter bar: Platform | Status | Date range
- Each thumbnail: PostThumbnailCard component
- Click → slide-in sheet (shadcn Sheet) with full post detail + PhoneMockup

### Drafts (`/drafts`)
- Card list with Approve / Reject / Schedule actions
- Bulk action toolbar
- PhoneMockup in right panel updates on card hover/focus

### Scheduler (`/scheduler`)
- Calendar grid (use `react-big-calendar` or custom shadcn approach)
- Drag-to-reschedule with Framer Motion
- Click day → quick-add post drawer

### Analytics (`/analytics`)
- Recharts line/bar charts for reach and engagement
- Competitor insights bento grid (Magic UI Bento style)
- Platform breakdown donut chart

---

## Code Style Rules

- **Functional components only** — no class components
- **TypeScript strict mode** — define all API response types in `types/api.ts`
- **Server Components by default** — add `'use client'` only when needed 
  (interactivity, hooks, Framer Motion)
- **File naming**: `kebab-case` for files, `PascalCase` for components
- **No inline styles** — Tailwind only, extend config for custom values
- **Error boundaries** on all data-fetching pages
- **Loading skeletons** using shadcn `<Skeleton>` on all async content

---

## Do NOT Do
- Do not use Material UI, Ant Design, or Bootstrap
- Do not use `pages/` router — App Router only
- Do not hardcode Flask URLs in components — use env var `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE`
- Do not use `any` TypeScript type — use `unknown` and narrow
- Do not skip loading/error states
